    <h3>A Technical Proposal is Not a Technical Document</h3>
    <p>Technical professionals often write proposals like they write reports, hyper-focussing on technical details. But a proposal is not a technical document. Its purpose is to persuade the client to award you the project, and the client can't do that unless you present an offer that demonstrates your understanding of the project, its stakeholders, and the client beyond the technical details and beyond what your competitors can offer. Your proposal must inspire the client's confidence that you can deliver a technical solution by managing non-technical elements of the work, such as responding to sudden changes, maintaining the schedule, and managing the least technical thing in the world - people.
</p>
